{
  "id": "019d286a-f2d8-78b2-92cd-5492c198a543",
  "content": "  match r.entry.entry_status {\n        EntryStatus::Merged => true,\n        EntryStatus::Pending | EntryStatus::Committed => {\n            match visibility {\n                VisibilityMode::Own => {\n                    match (agent_id, &r.entry.agent_id) {\n                        (Some(aid), Some(entry_aid)) => aid == entry_aid,\n                        _ => false,\n                    }\n                }\n                VisibilityMode::All => true,\n                VisibilityMode::Explicit(agents) => {\n                    match &r.entry.agent_id {\n                        Some(entry_aid) => agents.iter().any(|a| a == entry_aid),\n                        None => false,\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        EntryStatus::Rejected => false,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Add module to lib.rs**\n\nIn `crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs`, add after `pub mod rag_types;`:\n\n```rust\npub mod retriever;\n```\n\n**Step 5: Run tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p corvia-kernel -- retriever::tests --nocapture`\nExpected: all 3 tests PASS\n\n**Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/retriever.rs crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m3.2): Retriever trait + VectorRetriever — vector search with visibility filtering\"\n```\n\n---\n",
